= SDL_JoystickIsHaptic =
Use this function to check to see if a joystick has haptic features.


== Syntax ==
```c++
int SDL_JoystickIsHaptic(SDL_Joystick* joystick)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''joystick'''
|^a pointer to the^ joystick to test for haptic capabilities
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns 1 if the joystick is haptic, 0 if it isn't, or -1 if an error ''occurred''; call [[SDL_GetError]]() for more information.

